$interpreted: Crushfang: Colonel Augustinus, what's your business here?
Jahan: I heard you captured a wanted criminal from our Kingdom.
Jahan: Hand him over to me so I can bring him back for trial!
Crushfang: I informed Dylan. We wait for him.
Jahan: Who gives a damn about Dylan? If it's army ranks you're after, you should listen to me.
Jahan: Now, hand me the perp!
Crushfang: ...Afraid not.
Jahan: You animals, we'll turn your precious caves inside out!
Crushfang: I dare you!
Jahan: Dylan! Thank god you're here!  These bears are trying to harbor a wanted criminal.
Jahan: Apprehend them all!
Dylan: Colonel Augustinus, next time I hope you wait for me to show up before acting.
Jahan: What's with that attitude!?
Crushfang: Since Dylan is here, let's get to work.
Crushfang: You should recognize this.
Dylan: The emblem of the Kingdom? Judging from its appearance, it likely belongs to a high-ranking general.
Crushfang: The miner we captured had this on him.
Dylan: Where is this person?
Crushfang: Bring him out!
Dylan: His name was Tyr. Discharged from the army ten years ago. No news of him ever since.
Crushfang: I see. Colonel Augustinus, do you know anything about this?
Jahan: Of c-c-course, he became an outlaw after being discharged and started working in black-market mining.
Jahan: That's why we're in a hurry to arrest him. He is no longer a citizen of the Kingdom of the Sun!
Crushfang: Yet he still carries its emblem?
Dylan: Very suspicious indeed.
Crushfang: Could he be working with someone from the kingdom, trying to steal minerals from Totemtaff?
Jahan: We will know after his interrogation. No need for a bear like you to worry!
Crushfang: I will only hand him over to Dylan. What's done next is up to him.
Jahan: You mangy mongrel...
Dylan: Understood, I will make sure no stone is left unturned.
Dylan: I will inform you if anything comes up.
Crushfang: Thank you, also please take Colonel Augustinus with you.
Jahan: What do you mean "take"? I am my own person, thank you very much!
Crushfang: Hmph... I can sense a storm on the horizon...
